#CHIP C140
#CLOCK 6000000

; C140 (Namco 163) Basic Test
;
; The C140 is a Namco custom chip used in various arcade games.
; It has 8 channels of 8-bit PCM playback with a fixed sample rate.
;
; Note: The actual C140 has 24 channels in some configurations.
; This test targets the basic 8-channel variant.
;
; Tests:
; - All 8 channels with basic sample playback
; - Various waveforms (square, sawtooth, noise if supported)
; - Volume control

#TRACK 0

TEMPO 120

; Channel 1: Sample 1
c4 .

; Channel 2: Sample 2
d4 .

; Channel 3: Sample 3
e4 .

; Channel 4: Sample 4
f4 .

r4

; All 8 channels together
c4 & d4 & e4 & f4 & g4 & a4 & b4 & c5 .

r4

; Staccato pattern
c4 . d4 . e4 . f4 .

r2

#END
